H3.text: dendrites and cell bodies are components of what type of matter found in the brain. gray

A4.text: Grey matter is distinguished from white matter in that it contains numerous cell bodies and relatively few myelinated axons, while white matter contains relatively few cell bodies and is composed chiefly of long-range myelinated axons.

A5.text: Grey matter refers to unmyelinated neurons and other cells of the central nervous system.
